title: 'Life-threatening': California braces for first tropical storm in 84 years
description: California is bracing for its first tropical storm in 84 years with almost 1,000 flights cancelled and the ongoing actors' strike called off due to the impending extreme weather.

title: Tenerife wildfire that's forced thousands from homes started deliberately - officials
description: A wildfire raging on Tenerife was started deliberately, officials have said.

title: Spain's World Cup match-winner found out father had died after game
description: The Spanish star who scored the match-winning goal against England in Sunday's World Cup final found out her father had died after the game.

description: British heptathlon star Katarina Johnson-Thompson has clinched gold at the World Athletics Championship.

description: This isn't how it was meant to end for England.

title: Two men die in Ironman competition
description: Two men have died at an Ironman competition in Ireland.

title: Heartbreak for England as Lionesses miss out on World Cup glory after defeat to Spain
description: England's Lionesses have missed out on glory at the Women's World Cup after being beaten 1-0 by Spain.

title: Police intervene to stop pre-G20 meeting after Modi criticised
description: Indian police have intervened to stop a conference where the country's prime minister Narendra Modi was accused of using the upcoming G20 leaders' summit to boost his party's chances in next year's general election.

title: Russia's Luna-25 spacecraft 'crashes into moon'
description: Russia has reported that its Luna-25 spacecraft which launched earlier this month has crashed into the moon.

title: At least 18 dead and others injured as bus bursts into flames after crash
description: At least 18 people have died and 16 are injured after a bus caught fire in the eastern Punjab province of Pakistan.
